<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1407,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Second flagellomere with subapical style; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[829,854,1425,1439]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2+3</subScript>
arising from Rs about ¾ of the distance between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1425,1439]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1</subScript>
and r-m; genital fork V-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,324]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1479,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Description. Head.</emphasis>
Narrower than thorax; male and female dichoptic; ocellar triangle from light brown to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose. Frons longer than wide (2.0X longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1924" box="[1084,1190,1516,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[1084,1190,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), medially depressed. Face yellow to dark brown. Proboscis dark yellow to dark brown. Postcranium mainly light brown to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose, covered by sparse setae. Antenna brown to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose; scape small; pedicel near as long as wide (as long as wide in 
<emphasis box="[775,1013,1624,1649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melander" authorityYear="1961" box="[775,894,1624,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Mythicomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">P. angusta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1924" box="[906,1013,1624,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">P. minuta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
); first flagellomere oval or coniform, generally longer than wide (wider than long in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1924" box="[683,789,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[683,789,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); second flagellomere with subapical style. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1286,1382,1660,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Thorax.</emphasis>
Mesonotum brown to dark brown (light brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira, 2019" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" box="[682,818,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parakake" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[682,699,1696,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[714,818,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">parakake</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[827,917,1696,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[827,917,1696,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), subshiny to matte, yellowish gray pruinose; yellow marks on: postpronotal lobe, postalar callus (dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evenhuis" authorityYear="2002" box="[898,1026,1732,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavitibia">
<emphasis box="[898,1026,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. flavitibia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evenhuis" authorityYear="2002" box="[1079,1238,1732,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dominicana">
<emphasis box="[1079,1238,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. dominicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and notopleuron (dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evenhuis" authorityYear="2002" box="[327,487,1768,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dominicana">
<emphasis box="[327,487,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. dominicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Scutellum yellow to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose; anepisternum brown to dark brown (light brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira, 2019" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" box="[465,601,1804,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parakake" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[465,482,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[497,601,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">parakake</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,700,1804,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,700,1804,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), yellowish gray pruinose, with varying patterns of yellow areas. Legs yellow to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose; coxae with yellow setae on anteroventral surface; tibiae yellow (posterior tibia dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melander" authorityYear="1961" box="[541,658,1876,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Mythicomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[541,658,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[682,754,1875,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Wing.</emphasis>
Hyaline to slightly smoky, veins yellow to brown; C ending between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[270,296,1929,1943]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[369,377,1929,1943]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1</subScript>
; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[410,435,1929,1943]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2+3</subScript>
arising from Rs in about ¾ of distance between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[995,1003,1929,1943]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1</subScript>
and r-m, arising in angle of 60º to 80º; dm complete, apically narrow; posterior veins of medial and anal areas reaching wing margin; A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1265,1273,1965,1979]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2</subScript>
absent. Halter whitish yellow to brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,563,1983,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites light yellow to dark brown, yellowish gray pruinose; tergites usually with whitish yellow to yellow band on posterior margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[783,982,152,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Ejaculatory apodeme cross shaped, with medial arms well developed; anterior arm of parameral sheath spatulate; basiphallus conical, distiphallus ventrally curved (not curved in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira, 2019" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" box="[398,504,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeatesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[398,504,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">P. yeatesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[511,600,225,251]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[511,600,225,251]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Gonostylus conspicuous or not. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1078,225,251]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Female.</emphasis>
Genital fork V-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,324]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,260,287]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Geographic records.</emphasis>
Nearctic (
<collectingCountry box="[556,612,261,287]" name="United States of America" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">USA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[665,752,261,288]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Mexico</collectingCountry>
) and Neotropical (
<collectingCountry box="[958,1065,261,287]" name="Bahamas" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1076,1147,261,287]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1220,261,287]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Chile</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1231,1327,261,287]" name="Curaçao" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Curacao</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1337,1432,261,287]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,387,297,323]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[506,594,297,323]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[605,726,297,324]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
